quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  3,113,"Not are they all alike. Of the people of the Book there are a community steadfast, reciting the revelations of Allah in the hours of night while they prostrate themselves"
  3,114,"And they believe in Allah and the Last Day and command that which is reputable and prohibit that which is disreputable, and vie with each other to virtues. And these are of the righteous"
  3,115,And whatsoever they do of virtue shall not be denied. And Allah is Knower of the God-fearing
  3,116,"Verily those who disbelieve, neither their riches nor their progeny shall avail them aught against Allah. And these are the fellows of the Fire; thereinto they shall be abiders"
  3,117,"The likeness of that which they expend in this life of the world is as the likeness of a wind wherein is intense cold, it befalleth the tilth of a people who have wronged themselves, and destroyeth it. Allah wronged them not, but themselves they wrong"
  3,118,"O Ye who believe! take not for an intimate anyone besides yourselves; they shall not be remiss in doing you mischief. Fain would they that which distresseth you. Surely their malice hath shewn itself by their mouths, and that which their breasts conceal is greater still. Surely We have expounded unto you the signs, if ye will but reflect"
  3,119,"Lo! it is you who love them whereas they love you not, and you believe in the Book, all of it. When they meet you, they say: we believe. And when they are alone, they bite their fingertips at you in rage. Say thou: die in your rage. Verily Allah is Knower of that which is in the breasts"
  3,120,"If there happenoth unto you any good it grieveth them, and if there happenoth unto you an ill, they rejoice thereat. And if ye remain persevering and God-fearing their guile shall not harm you at all. Verily Allah is of that which they work Encompasser"
  3,121,"And recall what time thou settedst forth from thy household early to settle believers in positions for the fight. And Allah is Hearing, Knowing"
  3,122,"Recall what time two sections of you bethought that they should flag whereas Allah was the Patron of the twain. In Allah, then, let the believers trust"
  3,123,And assuredly Allah had succoured you at Badr While ye were humble. Wherefore fear Allah that haply ye may return thanks
  3,124,"And Recall what time thou saidst to the believers: sufficieth it not unto that your lord should reinforce you with three thousand angels sent down"
  3,125,"O Yea! if ye but remain persevering and God-fearing, and they should come upon you in this rush of theirs, your Lord shall reinforce you with five thousand angels marked"
  3,126,"And this Allah made not except as a joyful enunciation unto you, and that thereby your hearts might be set at rest--and no succour is there but from before Allah, the Mighty, the Wise"
  3,127,"That He may cut: off a portion of those who disbelieve, or abase them so that they may go back disappointed"
  3,128,"Not with thee is aught of the affair: He shall either relent toward them or torment them, for verily they are wrong-doers"
  3,129,"Allah's is whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth. He forgiveth whomsoever He listeth, and tormenteth whomsoever He listeth. And Allah is Forgiving, Merciful"
  3,130,"O Ye who believe! devour not multiplied manifold; and fear usury, Allah, haply ye may fare well"
  3,131,And beware of the Fire gotten ready for the infidels
  3,132,"And obey Allah and the apostle, haply ye may be shewn mercy"